also the local government has to introduce

140
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:05,463
some changes in their procurement.
So we will hear a lot in the coming years

141
00:08:05,663 --> 00:08:10,491
on innovative public procurement,
which is another challenging area

142
00:08:10,503 --> 00:08:14,086
I would say, because as we all
know by now,

143
00:08:14,111 --> 00:08:19,267
this Smart City projects,
the implementation of these solutions

144
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:25,382
are long term projects and
financing is another big challenge.

145
00:08:25,407 --> 00:08:29,696
So who finances innovation?
Sometimes the local administration,

146
00:08:29,896 --> 00:08:32,353
makes the push and the first move.

147
00:08:33,494 --> 00:08:41,856
But then these lead to maintenance,
so innovative procurement, financing,

148
00:08:42,435 --> 00:08:46,467
integration of the existing
with the new approaches

149
00:08:46,667 --> 00:08:48,732
these are three,
and I would add four.

150
00:08:48,769 --> 00:08:50,176
There's probably more.

151
00:08:50,176 --> 00:08:52,698
But a fourth would be

152
00:08:53,201 --> 00:08:58,639
how to really make
the citizens participate

153
00:08:59,035 --> 00:09:04,723
not only be informed that their city
is working towards innovation,

154
00:09:04,748 --> 00:09:09,498
efficiency, sustainability,
but really how to make them

155
00:09:09,498 --> 00:09:14,774
participate in the equation
because it's a long-term project

156
00:09:14,786 --> 00:09:18,031
where all the stakeholders
need to be involved.

157
00:09:18,962 --> 00:09:22,180
Great.
I also know that

158
00:09:22,192 --> 00:09:24,840
you have been involved
in all these European projects,

159
00:09:24,857 --> 00:09:26,381
not only in Barcelona.

160
00:09:26,382 --> 00:09:27,279
And the lessons

161
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:29,298
from Barcelona
